Title: Understanding Flexbox in CSS

Content: Flexbox is a powerful layout module in CSS that allows you to design complex layouts with ease. Unlike traditional block and inline layout models, Flexbox enables you to align and distribute space among items in a container, even when their sizes are unknown or dynamic.

Flexbox is particularly useful when creating responsive designs. It provides greater control over the alignment, direction, and order of elements. In this post, we'll explore the basics of Flexbox, including the main properties you'll use and some practical examples...
